{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "3d8a6f0b-9f8f-4d42-8d8c-6d4c4c8b3a10",
    "name": "Dllni - User Module (SMS OTP Auth) - v1",
    "description": "## Base\n- `{{baseUrl}}` defaults to `http://Dllni.test`\n- All endpoints are prefixed with `/api/v1/user/*`\n\n## Flow overview\n### Register + verify\n1. `POST /register` creates the user then sends OTP to the phone.\n2. `POST /verify-account` verifies OTP and returns a Sanctum token.\n\n### Login (SMS OTP)\n1. `POST /login` checks password then sends OTP.\n2. `POST /login/verify` verifies OTP and returns a Sanctum token.\n\n### Reset password (SMS OTP)\n1. `POST /reset-password` sends OTP if the phone exists.\n2. `POST /reset-password/confirm` verifies OTP, updates password, and returns a token.\n\n## Auth\n- After you get a token, set `{{token}}` and use it as `Authorization: Bearer {{token}}` where needed.\n\n## Notes\n- SMS provider is abstracted behind a provider interface so you can plug in a Syrian SMS provider later.\n",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Register",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register (send OTP)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json"
              },
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Test User\",\n  \"email\": \"test.user@example.com\",\n  \"phone\": \"+963944000111\",\n  \"password\": \"password123\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/user/register",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "user",
                "register"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Creates a new user and sends an SMS OTP for account verification.\n\n**Response**:\n- `message`\n- `expiresAt` (ISO 8601)"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Verify account (OTP) -> token",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json"
              },
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"phone\": \"+963944000111\",\n  \"otp\": \"123456\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/user/verify-account",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "user",
                "verify-account"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Verifies the registration OTP, marks the account as verified, and returns a Sanctum token.\n\n**Response**:\n- `user`\n- `token`"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
